<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3682] SYSCS_BULK_INSERT doesn&apos;t quote identifiers or strings properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3682</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Discovered by Mamta A. Satoor in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1062&quot; title=&quot;Change the internal implemetation of SYSCS_INPLACE_COMPRESS_TABLE to share existing alter table&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1062&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1062&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SYSCS_BULK_INSERT builds an insert statement in which it doesn&apos;t quote the schema name or the table name. It also takes string parameters that are inserted into the statement text with single quotes around them, but that won&apos;t work if those strings contain single quote characters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12396476">DERBY-3682</key>
            <summary>SYSCS_BULK_INSERT doesn&apos;t quote identifiers or strings properly</summary>
